<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0893 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the Federal Republic of Germany sanitary landfills (municipal wastesand refuse similar to municipal wastes) are in most cases equipped withfacilities controlling the release of gaseous emissions. The paper refersto the utilization of landfill gases and points out the uses realizedso far on an industrial scale: a) water heating, space heating and processheat production through waste combustion; b) electric power generationin waste heat recovering gas engines (cogeneration); c) gases which convertedwith the help of absorption, adsorption or membrane separation processingprocedures are compatible with natural gas. A brief survey informs aboutfurther uses and the developments expected for the future.</TEXT></DOC>